16/03/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- President Stipe Mesic approved on Monday (15 March) the appointment of Josko Podbevsek as director of the Counterintelligence Agency (POA). The appointment has already received the approval of Prime Minister Ivo Sanader. Last week, both Mesic and Sanader signed off on a move to replace Franjo Turek as POA director, at his own request.
In other news, the UN refugee agency agreed on Monday to provide support for the process of returning Croatian refugees to their homeland. The agreement came during a meeting between Mesic and UN Assistant High Commissioner for Refugees Kamel Morjane. (HINA - 15/03/04)
